# Relationship Integrity Rule™ (Platform Law — 141)

**Constitution bridge:** `docs/constitution/117_TRUST_MEMORY_AND_RELATIONSHIP_CONSTITUTION.md` · Article in `113`  
**Binds:** Spec **117** Business Brain · Spec **128** · Spec **132** · Intelligence Blueprint  
**Certification:** `docs/platform/141_*`  
**Runtime:** `lib/intelligence/relationshipIntegrity.ts` · `ensureCreateLineage.ts`

## Principle

**Everything Knows What It Belongs To.** One business memory, many windows.

Relationships preserve trust. Spark must never invent edges from similar names or titles alone.

## Allowed edge sources (only these)

1. **Creation flow lineage** — Work created from a Project, Blueprint, Map node, or explicit related Work id  
2. **Explicit user link** — member chose Connect / Related To  
3. **Shared Work / Project context** — already on the same Work or Project container  
4. **User confirmation** — when a match is ambiguous, ask before linking  

## Forbidden

- Auto-creating graph edges from title / name similarity alone  
- Fuzzy “looks related” linking without confirmation  
- Duplicate linking that invents a second Work body  
- Surfacing invented connections in Projects hub, Pulse, or Related To  

## Suggestion vs edge

`findRelatedWork` may surface `similar_title_or_intent` / `same_work_type` as **suggestions** for duplicate-risk UI.

Those signals must call `relationshipLinkDecision()` — they are **never** sufficient alone for durable edges.

## Projects hub

Surface related Work / Maps / Strategies / Conversations / Evidence / Wins **only** when store hooks or trusted edges already exist (`projectRelatedWork.ts`).

## Before shipping relationship UI or auto-link

- [ ] Edge has a trusted `edgeSource`?  
- [ ] No title-only invention?  
- [ ] Ambiguous → confirm with member?  
- [ ] Deduped (no duplicate Work identity)?  
- [ ] Passes trust (117) and momentum (132)?  
